JO  - The Journal of Finance
JA  - The Journal of Finance
SP  - 1909
EP  - 1930
VL  - 51
IS  - 5
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0022-1082
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1540-6261.1996.tb05231.x
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - ABSTRACT This study analyzes the effects of changes in S&P 500 index composition from January 1986 through June 1994, a period during which Standard and Poor's began its practice of preannouncing changes five days beforehand. The new announcement practice has given rise to the ?S&P game? and has altered the way stock prices react. We find that prices increase abnormally from the close on the announcement day to the close on the effective day. The overall increase is greater than under the old announcement policy although part of the increase reverses after the stock is included in the index.
ER  - 

TY  - JOUR
T1  - The Wealth Effects of Bank Financing Announcements in Highly Leveraged Transactions
AU  - KRACAW, WILLIAM A.
AU  - ZENNER, MARC
Y1  - 1996/12/01
PY  - 1996
DA  - 1996/12/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1540-6261.1996.tb05232.x
